President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring June 2016 as Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, and Transgender (LGBT) Pride Month. The proclamation recognizes the progress made in advancing the rights and equality of LGBT individuals, including the landmark Supreme Court decision legalizing same-sex marriage. The Obama Administration is committed to understanding and addressing the needs of LGBT adults, providing housing for aging LGBT Americans, opposing conversion therapy for minors, promoting equality in schools, and addressing health disparities in the LGBT community. The President also urges Congress to pass legislation prohibiting discrimination against LGBT individuals and emphasizes the importance of promoting LGBT rights globally. The proclamation calls for the elimination of prejudice and celebrates the diversity of the American people.